The paper deals with the problem of learning the parameters of a Poisson Binomial Distribution (PBD) and provides lower and upper bounds on the query complexity for this problem. This problem falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses techniques from statistics and probability theory, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and statistics (cs.ST).
